iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories &nbsp;Lilongwe - Pop star Madonna has filed for the adoption of two more children from Malawi.A government spokesperson says the singer appeared before a High Court judge on Wednesday.Spokesperson Mlenga Mvula says it is now up to the court to decide whether to grant the adoption order. The singer will have to wait a week before hearing the decision on her application.Madonna in 2008 adopted David Banda and a year later adopted Mercy James.The pop star in 2006 founded the charity Raising Malawi to address the poverty and hardship endured by this southern African country's orphans and vulnerable children.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.